metadata.name: Inertia #1338
metadata.description:
This project will be reserved and free for 48 hours, for all the holders of any of my projects!

The amount of reserves for each user will be equal to the amount of all the token held at 13:00 CEST [UTC+2] (May 23)
(example: user holds 3 "Figment" and 2 "ACCUMULATOR", will be able to mint "Inertia" 5 times)

48h from now I will update the reserves list and burn the remaining tokens

WARINING: The reserves will expire 48h after the drop! And a price for the unlocked mintables will be set (unreserved mints will not be free).

---

"Inertia is a property of matter by which it continues in its existing state of rest or uniform motion in a straight line, unless that state is changed by an external force."

Particles are blasted from 2 to 4 sides of the canvas, each particle has its own mass and it has to traverse a friction-field, once it loses its momentum completely it stops and leaves a trace, adding or subtracting light from the canvas.

The friction-field has 18 possible mutation kinds.
Mutations are high-friction zones of various shapes.

Made just with JS on a canvas
right-click to save

metadata.name: A24Z #119
metadata.description:
Every artist and collector feels the joy of both creating and collecting. But if I could share the joy of creating with collectors. And collectors with their family and friends, what may be an additive process of joy is now perhaps exponential. Joy to the power of 26 to be exact. 

In this work I invite my friends and collectors to collaborate with me. Though not in coding, but together in a process of creating narratives and visuals. Code and story. We didn’t use github, just a simple p5.js editor to try out different programs and palettes. Pedrofe and J0rdan pick their palettes tastefully and carefully. okeoke, perhaps more of a genius than he lets on, picks his palettes blind. No hex color picker. Just straight up rhymes.  

In our discussions verbal language was forbidden. Only emojis were allowed to express our tastes and views. Each emojis put down on google doc was taken with absolutely seriousness. 

Pedro: Loves to taking his daily walks on “Magic Mushroom Mountain”

J0rdan: Wonders about “Quark Question Quiches”

Okeoke: Just get lost in “Finnegans’ Flower Fields.”

It has been a great joy to present our illustration book A24Z, 8 more than you know who. Each page expresses the alphabet with the best of our knowledge in semantics and sarcasm. Collect just 1 page, collect the alphabets that spell out your name, collect the whole A to Z. Read it to your children or loved ones. Though you might need to interpolate or extrapolate with great imagination which children all have. But most importantly, like all children, have fun!

Press 1 to save png, only for Chrome, not Safari. Preview images are compressed or broken, test capture at 300 sec.

metadata.name: FairyCells #24
metadata.description:
FairyCells is a series created by a generative system, displaying shapes, between 1 and 10, made up of three different color palettes. 
Cells cannot cross each other, and are composed of a flat tint and/or a hatch system.

You can right-click to download an SVG file of the NFT or press « E » to export as png (3401x3401px)

Moreover, the digital version can exist as a physical piece.
Owning the NFT gives the right to order, in addition, a 30x30cm plotter drawing of it. More information about it here: https://nft.julienespagnon.fr/fairy-cells.
You can see some test examples plotted in the google form: https://docs.google.com/forms/d/1FO3Umh49qmJApZAlQgZ46a2y421QYEWIW8r72nLrW4Q/edit

Work by Julien Espagnon - 2021/2022

metadata.name: Z'YDRON #70
Supremacy Reborn #18
metadata.description:
We're rising right now.
The Big Bang theory is the prevailing cosmological model explaining the existence of the observable universe from the earliest known periods to its subsequent large-scale evolution. The universe expanded from an initial state of high density and temperature, and offers a comprehensive explanation of a wide range of observable phenomena. However, this picture describes what happened up to this point. The beginning of the expansion of the Universe, before which the universe was in a singular state. Inspired by "Singularity" of Hideki Tsukamoto and Guides of @degenerative_art

Press Space to animate the image.

Press S to save the image.

Made with p5.js
